summary: An Ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 13530, entitled "An Ordinance authorizing and directing the Board of Public Works to the City of Seattle to provide for the removal of all deed animals within the City of Seattle, and to property dispose of the same, and to enter into contracts for the removal and disposition of such dead animal, and repealing all ordinances, and parts of ordinances, in conflict herewith", approved April 11, 1906.
